Total number of syllables: 149
Total number of words: 65
Total number of sentences: 9

Now, to compute the LIX score:

1. Calculate the average number of words per sentence:
Words per sentence = Total number of words / Total number of sentences
= 65 / 9
= 7.22 (round to 2 decimal places)

2. Calculate the average number of syllables per word:
Syllables per word = Total number of syllables / Total number of words
= 149 / 65
= 2.29 (round to 2 decimal places)

3. Calculate the LIX score:
LIX = Words per sentence + (Syllables per word x 0.4)
= 7.22 + (2.29 x 0.4)
= 7.22 + 0.916
= 8.14

Rounded to one decimal place, the result is:
LIX=8.1